<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900914-0046</DOCNO><DOCID>900914-0046.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- United Technologies Corp.:   Sikorsky Unit Will Lay Off   350 White-Collar Employees</HL><DATE>09/14/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   UTX</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp.,said it will lay off 350 white-collar employees Saturday inorder to make the company more competitive.   The helicopter manufacturer said the layoffs, concentratedin the Connecticut area, include engineers and administrativepersonnel. &quot;We decided to size the company to be leaner andmore competitive, after looking at different segments of thebusiness,&quot; a spokesman said. The cuts reduce Sikorsky's workforce to 11,300.</LP><TEXT>   Last February, the company, based in Stratford, Conn.,laid off 300 white-collar workers as a reaction to cuts indefense spending. Fifty hourly workers were laid off inMarch, and another 50 were cut through attrition that month.   In the second quarter, United Technologies earningsincreased 51% to $207.5 million, or $1.64 a share.   Sikorsky Aircraft has operations in Bridgeport, WestHaven, Shelton and Trumbull, Conn., as well as Troy, Ala.,and West Palm Beach, Fla. Its major military products includethe Black Hawk and Super Stallion helicopters.</TEXT></DOC>